Resident Engagement Scores 2016-2017

Brian Gulbis

June 14, 2017

library(tidyverse)
library(forcats)
library(themebg)
library(plotly)

scores <- read_rds("../data/final/scores.Rds")
scores %>%
    arrange(Score) %>%
    mutate_at("Item", fct_inorder) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = Item, y = Score)) +
    geom_bar(aes(fill = Domain), stat = "identity") +
    geom_hline(yintercept = 3.62, color = "grey35") +
    geom_hline(yintercept = 3.62 + 0.65, color = "grey20", linetype = "dashed") +
    xlab("") +
    scale_y_continuous("Score", limits = c(0, 5), breaks = seq(0, 5, 1)) +
    scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Dark2") +
    coord_flip() +
    theme_bg(yticks = FALSE) +
    theme(legend.position = c(0, 1), 
          legend.justification = c(1, 0),
          legend.direction = "horizontal",
          plot.margin = unit(c(5, 1, 0.5, 0.5), "lines"))

Aggregate score for each question. Solid line indicates overall score, dashed line indicates overall employee score. 

# ggplotly(p, dynamicTicks = TRUE)
scores %>%
    arrange(Compare_Overall) %>%
    # top_n(-10, Score) %>%
    mutate_at("Item", fct_inorder) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = Item, y = Compare_Overall)) +
    geom_bar(aes(fill = Domain), stat = "identity") +
    geom_hline(yintercept = 0, color = "grey65") +
    xlab("") +
    ylab("Difference Relative to Overall Score") +
    scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Dark2") +
    coord_flip() +
    theme_bg(yticks = FALSE) +
    theme(legend.position = c(0, 1), 
          legend.justification = c(1, 0),
          legend.direction = "horizontal",
          plot.margin = unit(c(5, 1, 0.5, 0.5), "lines"))

Resident engagement score by question compared to overall employee score. 

# ggplotly(p, dynamicTicks = TRUE)
scores %>%
    arrange(Score) %>%
    top_n(10, Score) %>%
    mutate_at("Item", fct_inorder) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = Item, y = Score)) +
    geom_bar(aes(fill = Domain), stat = "identity") +
    xlab("") +
    scale_y_continuous("Score", limits = c(0, 5), breaks = seq(0, 5, 1)) +
    scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Dark2") +
    coord_flip() +
    theme_bg(yticks = FALSE) +
    theme(legend.position = c(0, 1), 
          legend.justification = c(1, 0),
          legend.direction = "horizontal",
          plot.margin = unit(c(5, 1, 0.5, 0.5), "lines"))

Top 10 questions by score (areas of strength).

Bottom 10 questions by score (areas of concern). 

scores %>%
    filter(Favorable >= 0.8) %>%
    arrange(Favorable, Score) %>%
    # top_n(10, Favorable) %>%
    mutate_at("Favorable", funs(. * 100)) %>%
    mutate_at("Item", fct_inorder) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = Item, y = Favorable)) +
    geom_bar(aes(fill = Domain), stat = "identity") +
    xlab("") +
    scale_y_continuous("Residents with Favorable Score (%)") +
    scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Dark2") +
    coord_flip() +
    theme_bg(yticks = FALSE) +
    theme(legend.position = c(0, 1), 
          legend.justification = c(1, 0),
          legend.direction = "horizontal",
          plot.margin = unit(c(5, 1, 0.5, 0.5), "lines"))

Questions with 8 or more residents answering with a favorable score 

scores %>%
    filter(Unfavorable >= 0.3) %>%
    arrange(Unfavorable, desc(Score)) %>%
    # top_n(10, Unfavorable) %>%
    mutate_at("Unfavorable", funs(. * 100)) %>%
    mutate_at("Item", fct_inorder) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = Item, y = Unfavorable)) +
    geom_bar(aes(fill = Domain), stat = "identity") +
    xlab("") +
    scale_y_continuous("Residents with Unfavorable Score (%)") +
    scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Dark2") +
    coord_flip() +
    theme_bg(yticks = FALSE) +
    theme(legend.position = c(0, 1), 
          legend.justification = c(1, 0),
          legend.direction = "horizontal",
          plot.margin = unit(c(5, 1, 0.5, 0.5), "lines"))

Questions with 3 or more residents answering with an unfavorable score
